provided.datapacket

Class ADataPacket

  • java.lang.Object
    • provided.extvisitor.AExtVisitorHost<java.lang.Class<?>,ADataPacket>
      • provided.datapacket.ADataPacket
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, IExtVisitorHost<java.lang.Class<?>,ADataPacket>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataPacket

    public abstract class ADataPacket
extends AExtVisitorHost<java.lang.Class<?>,ADataPacket>
    Abstract data packet that defines the use of a Class object as the index type. The type of data held by the data packet defines its type and thus what case it calls on its processing visitors.
    Author:
    Stephen Wong (c) 2010 * ---------------------------------------------- Specifies use of Class type for host ID
